1. Molim te da mi daš *blagoslov* za ovaj projekt. (Please give me your *blessing* for this project.)
2. Naša porodica je *blagoslovena* zdravljem i srećom. (Our family is *blessed* with health and happiness.)
3. Ova crkva je bila mesto gde su ljudi tražili *blagoslov* od Boga. (This church was a place where people sought *blessings* from God.)
4. Svi smo se molili da Bog *blagoslovi* ovaj brak. (We all prayed that God would *bless* this marriage.)
5. U Srbiji postoji običaj da starije osobe daju *blagoslov* mlađima. (In Serbia, it is a custom for older people to give their *blessing* to younger ones.)
6. Za Božić, sveštenik daje *blagoslov* domovima ljudi u svojoj parohiji. (For Christmas, the priest gives *blessing* to the homes of people in his parish.)
7. Na kraju službe, sveštenik je dao *blagoslov* vernicima. (At the end of the service, the priest gave *blessing* to the parishioners.)
8. Neka vas Bog *blagoslovi* i sačuva u svojoj milosti. (May God *bless* you and keep you in His grace.)
9. Ova zemlja ima bogatstvo prirodnih resursa, što je pravi *blagoslov*. (This country has a wealth of natural resources, which is a real *blessing*.)
10. Mnogi ljudi smatraju da su deca *blagoslov* i najveće bogatstvo u životu. (Many people believe that children are a *blessing* and the greatest wealth in life.)